2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: STEVEN KYLE DENTON, Ph.D.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: Manufacturing & Tech Executive | Digital Transformation | Operational Excellence | Enterprise Modernization
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: Arlington, VA | (253) 225-6124 | steven.k.denton@gmail.com | https://linkedin.com/in/skdenton
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: 
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: PROFESSIONAL PROFILE
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: Mission-driven executive with expertise spanning digital transformation, IT portfolio strategy, zero-trust cybersecurity, and large-scale modernization across manufacturing and engineering organizations. Recognized executive champion for leading global initiatives, building high-performing teams, and creating strategies that translate into action.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: Core Competencies:
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: • Product Lifecycle Management (PLM) • Manufacturing Execution Systems (MES) • Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP)
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: • Digital Transformation • Agile & Lean Manufacturing • Operational Excellence
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: • P&L / Budget Management • Industry 4.0 Smart Factory Tech • PLM / ERP / MES Integration
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: • Supply Chain Modernization • Advanced Manufacturing • Predictive Maintenance
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: • Cybersecurity & Zerotrust • Data Analytics & Machine Learning • AI and Automation
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: • Strategic Planning • Program Management • Executive Communication
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: RECENT EXPERIENCE
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: Senior Portfolio Director Dec 2024 – Present
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: Chief of Naval Operations Pentagon, Arlington, VA
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: Executive resource sponsor overseeing 94 program offices and $2.4B (R&D and operational funds) for in-service and enterprise modernization of industrial IT systems for engineering, manufacturing, lifecycle management, and maintenance of Naval aircraft, surface ships, nuclear submarines, nuclear aircraft carriers, and shore facilities.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.508 | Text body normalized: • Developed strategic roadmap aligning PLM and MES systems to commercial best practices for software acquisition.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Provided strategic advisory to flag officers and senior executives on software portfolio investment strategy, data integration, and cybersecurity risk management.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Authored senior leadership white papers and briefings influencing enterprise-level digital manufacturing, maintenance, and lifecycle management policy and funding decisions.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Industrial Operations Strategy Lead Jul 2024 – Dec 2024
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Naval Sea Systems Command Headquarters Washington Navy Yard, D.C.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Placed on 6-mo special assignment to D.C. as engineering and manufacturing executive to establish overarching strategy.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Facilitated flag officer and senior executive forums, engaged with transformation initiative leads and stakeholders, and built data-driven decision models to improve shipyard performance.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Developed Hub for Executive Leadership and Management through rapid low-code/no-code platform and agile development sprints, providing systematic alignment of initiatives and tasks across $6B industrial enterprise.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Received Letter of Commendation from Senior Executive Service.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Director, Digital Transformation and Modernization 2020 – 2024
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Puget Sound Naval Shipyard Bremerton, WA
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Led modernization of one of the nation’s largest industrial manufacturing and maintenance enterprises (6,700 employees, $800M operating budget). Directed the digital enablement of production, engineering, and logistics operations, facilitating partnerships with Deloitte, MIT, Stanford, and other major defense technology vendors.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Digitized 85% of frontline operations by deploying 1,400 mobile devices, 1,000 tablets, and 500 digital work hubs – improving data flow, safety, and readiness across shipyard industrial operations.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Reduced administrative labor by 50,400 hours/year through "Digital Crew Board” & automation initiatives.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Authored and executed enterprise-wide Digital Transformation Strategy and established cross-functional governance structures for innovation and data science.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Directed COVID-19 remote-work transition and developed policy for 6,700 employees.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Recognized with Civilian Service Achievement Medal, NAVSEA Innovation Award, and U.S. Patent No. 11,243,368 for 3D-printed shipboard component design.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Industrial Program Manager 2016 – 2020
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Puget Sound Naval Shipyard Bremerton, WA
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: Oversaw quality, schedule, and budget performance for electrical, electronics, calibration, and metrology for manufacturing operations. Established and led the Navy’s first enterprise Fiber Optics Program and manufacturing standardization initiative.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Founded five certified manufacturing and training facilities across U.S. Naval Shipyards and Trident Refit Facility Bangor; certified 3,300 technicians, quality assurance personnel, and supervisors.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Achieved $14M in cost avoidance and 74% reduction in development time for certification processes.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Directed national Communities of Practice uniting 70+ engineering and production/manufacturing leaders for electrical, electronics, and calibration/metrology of Naval equipment and systems.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Earned Seattle Federal Executive Board Public Service Award, Employee of the Year for Valor, and NAVSEA Excellence Award.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: ADDITIONAL EXPERIENCE
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Over a decade of supervisory, management, and executive experience, managing up to 120 direct staff and influencing organizations of 6,000+ personnel, with global footprint.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.509 | Text body normalized: • Over a decade of industry experience working with technology startups, banking, real estate, and retail operations.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • Over a decade of experience work on multiple non-profit board executive, member, and volunteer roles in domestic and international NGOs.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • Graduate-level educator at Gonzaga University, teaching leadership, strategy, resilience, and technological innovation since 2018.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: EDUCATION & CREDENTIALS
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • Ph.D., Leadership Studies (Organizational Transformation and Technology) – Gonzaga University (2025)
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • M.A., Organizational Leadership – Gonzaga University (2018), Global Leadership Certification
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • B.S., Workforce Education & Development – Southern Illinois University Carbondale (2015)
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • Change Management Practitioner (Prosci), LEAN Six Sigma Greenbelt, Scaled Agile Framework Practitioner, Executive Data Science Specialization (Johns Hopkins University), Zero Trust Cybersecurity (GW Center for Excellence), Certified Social and Behavioral Researcher (CITI), Journeyman Electronics Mechanic (Dept of Labor)
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • Clearance: T3R SECRET / NATO SECRET reinvestigation 10/23/2029
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: PROFESSIONAL AFFILIATIONS
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • American Association for the Advancement of Science • Association of Leadership Educators
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • Gonzaga School of Leadership Studies Advisory Board • United States Naval Institute
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: PUBLICATIONS & SPEAKING ENGAGEMENTS
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: Author and speaker across domestic and international forums, with 40+ publications on digital transformation, leadership, and innovation in government, academia, and industry. Selected works and engagements include:
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • "Leading at Flank Speed: A Comparative Case Study of Digital Champions in the U.S. Navy,” Gonzaga University, 2025 – dissertation focused on understanding human-centered methods to accelerate digital transformation.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • "Virtual Champions Day: Championing the Culture of Change,” Navy Champions Network, 2023 – presented enterprise-scale adoption strategies for digital collaboration platforms across 80,000 users.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • Invited speaker, HackTheMachine, Office of Naval Research, 2021 – presented on data-driven design, modeling, and decision tools for complex integrated systems.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • "Navigating the VUCA World: Embracing Factfulness for Better Decision-Making in Federal Management,” Federal Managers Association, 2023 – executive-level analysis of decision frameworks for uncertainty and change.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • "Leading Team Change,” Federal Managers Association, 2022 – published practitioner insights on digital-era workforce transformation and lean process improvement.
2025-11-07 19:10:59.510 | Text body normalized: • "Flank Speed Adds New Protections for Community of Interest (COI) Data,” CHIPS: The Department of the Navy’s IT Magazine, 2024 – featured contributor on cybersecurity and digital platform modernization.
